--- "Karl" <aufever(-at-)prodigy.net> wrote:
>> I know that 78 child's cots were collapsible some how but I figured all of the
> cots would be the same size.  So how many different size child's cots were
> there for bay window buses?  And where am I gonna find the right size?
> 
>What part does not fit?
>All the bay cot canvas is the same size.  But they do shrink.....
>The bars are different lengths:
>68-73 are 56 1/4" long.
>74-75 are 57 1/4" long.
>76-79 are two piece collapsible, but the 74-75 will fit.... you just won't have a place to store them.
>The half moons are mounted higher up on the A and B pillars on 68-73 buses.
